WEBVTT

00:02.560 --> 00:07.360
You've both met bad men before.
The man we're about to meet is the devil.

00:07.480 --> 00:08.920
MOSLEY: Michael Gray.

00:09.040 --> 00:12.040
You lost all your cousin's money
in America playing the fool.

00:12.160 --> 00:17.120
And poor old Arthur Shelby
is afraid his wife will never return.

00:19.800 --> 00:24.440
There's a bullet,
and on it is carved the name McCavern.

00:27.200 --> 00:29.000
It's war you want,

00:29.120 --> 00:30.960
it's war you shall have.

00:31.080 --> 00:32.680
I've been talking to the Friends.

00:32.800 --> 00:34.480
One of the Friends is a man.

00:34.600 --> 00:37.080
He would die without his eyes.

00:37.200 --> 00:39.880
These hands belong to the devil!

00:40.000 --> 00:42.720
By the time
that baby draws its first breath,

00:42.840 --> 00:44.080
you and I will be done.

00:45.280 --> 00:46.400
THOMAS: You will be king.

00:56.520 --> 00:59.760
(ETHEREAL MUSIC)

01:13.560 --> 01:14.960
Happy or sad, Tommy?

01:30.840 --> 01:32.600
(ENGINE RUMBLES)

01:41.040 --> 01:42.280
Mr Shelby.

01:44.560 --> 01:48.560
My bullets ache
to get inside your tinker head.

01:50.920 --> 01:53.520
# Up to our knees in Fenian blood

01:53.640 --> 01:56.120
# Surrender or you'll die

01:56.240 --> 02:00.200
# We are the Brigton Derry Billy Boys. #

02:00.320 --> 02:03.040
(GUNSHOTS)

02:03.160 --> 02:04.760
(DUCKS QUACK)

02:35.160 --> 02:37.160
You know, it's a pity.

02:37.280 --> 02:38.960
I was looking forward to killing you.

02:40.600 --> 02:43.240
You're at the back of a long queue.

02:44.720 --> 02:46.920
My white flag is a flag of truce.

02:48.080 --> 02:50.040
Yours is more a flag of surrender.

02:51.840 --> 02:54.480
Whatever you say, Mr McCavern,
the colour is the same.

02:54.600 --> 02:55.760
The outcome is the same.

02:57.040 --> 02:59.120
I believe we've friends in common.

02:59.240 --> 03:00.680
We should postpone our war.

03:00.800 --> 03:03.200
Your brother left me a hand grenade.

03:03.320 --> 03:04.640
He sends his apologies.

03:04.760 --> 03:06.720
You left me land mines.

03:06.840 --> 03:09.640
For which I too apologise.

03:10.680 --> 03:12.680
Then peace it is.

03:12.800 --> 03:16.160
Your message said you wanted
to seal our truce with some business.

03:17.680 --> 03:21.000
Since we're men of similar interests
and distribution networks,

03:21.120 --> 03:23.680
I thought we might use
our temporary settlement

03:23.800 --> 03:25.800
for our mutual benefit.

03:25.920 --> 03:28.880
You stand in a yard full of scrap metal
and stolen goods,

03:29.000 --> 03:30.440
and you talk like a politician.

03:30.560 --> 03:33.960
No, nothing here is stolen, Mr McCavern.

03:34.080 --> 03:36.480
Charlie simply finds things
before they're lost.

03:39.040 --> 03:42.200
The nature of the deal
is explained in my proposal.

03:42.320 --> 03:45.920
I've booked you a suite
at the Midland Hotel.

03:46.040 --> 03:49.160
If you need anything in this city,
just mention my name.

03:50.320 --> 03:52.160
So you want to impress me, Mr Shelby?

03:53.440 --> 03:54.760
Isiah.

03:58.000 --> 04:02.640
Also in the envelope is a cheque
for £50O.

04:02.760 --> 04:06.480
For your wife.
She can use it to buy a black dress,

04:06.600 --> 04:09.440
rent a black horse with black feathers

04:09.560 --> 04:12.560
to pull a black carriage
with your body in it,

04:12.680 --> 04:15.560
should you break the terms
of the white flag.

04:16.880 --> 04:20.920
Now, please, enjoy the city
it's my hon our to represent.

04:44.840 --> 04:46.600
This week I've managed
to get to the people

04:46.720 --> 04:49.680
at York and Lincoln City.
I mean, they're the teams that are losing.

04:49.800 --> 04:50.800
I got to them.

04:52.200 --> 04:54.240
Right, go on. Go on, take your time.

04:54.360 --> 04:55.360
Mm.

04:56.880 --> 04:59.560
I got to the goalkeepers,
they all said £5 is enough.

04:59.680 --> 05:00.680
I, erm...

05:03.640 --> 05:06.920
I've written to the people
at Tranmere Rovers

05:07.040 --> 05:09.760
because the phone you put
into my...into my house stopped working.

05:09.880 --> 05:11.600
So I'm gonna need
another one of those.

05:11.720 --> 05:12.880
OK.

05:13.000 --> 05:17.200
Once we've got that fixed,
hey, then we'll have all the names

05:17.320 --> 05:21.960
and numbers
of the First Division referees.

05:22.080 --> 05:23.120
The First?

05:23.240 --> 05:24.280
Yeah.

05:24.400 --> 05:27.560
Ah, shit, shit, shit, shit.

05:27.680 --> 05:29.360
Come on, come on. Come on.

05:29.480 --> 05:32.240
Listen, listen to me. Come on now.

05:32.360 --> 05:34.000
No need for that. Hm?

05:34.120 --> 05:35.280
Yeah.

05:35.400 --> 05:37.920
We need you to find out
what they like.

05:38.040 --> 05:40.080
You know, what gets them going.

05:41.200 --> 05:44.560
Cos a lot of them are comfortable.
A fiver's nothing to them.

05:44.680 --> 05:46.920
We need you to find out
what they really like playing.

05:47.040 --> 05:48.240
Yes.

05:48.360 --> 05:50.440
See, cos we can offer them that.

05:50.560 --> 05:52.160
Oh, yeah. Shelby Company Limited,

05:52.280 --> 05:56.320
we can offer them
all the lovely things people like.

05:56.440 --> 05:57.520
Hm?

05:58.560 --> 06:03.840
We can also offer 'em protection
from the things they don't like.

06:05.120 --> 06:06.600
You ever touch my family...

06:08.080 --> 06:09.080
...ever...

06:12.840 --> 06:14.320
York.

06:14.440 --> 06:15.640
Lincoln.

06:15.760 --> 06:17.040
- Lincoln?
- Hm.

06:20.320 --> 06:21.320
Tranmere Rovers.

06:21.440 --> 06:22.760
Hm?

06:22.880 --> 06:24.360
Mm-hm.

06:26.280 --> 06:28.440
- Bye, Finn.
- Goodbye, brother.

06:31.080 --> 06:32.160
Shit.

06:50.840 --> 06:54.000
THOMAS: It's all right, Mrs Connors.
You can carry on. It's just my brother.

06:56.760 --> 06:59.200
So tell me how it happened?

06:59.320 --> 07:01.440
MRS CONNORS:
They were sleeping downstairs.

07:03.080 --> 07:05.160
And then my husband came home...

07:05.280 --> 07:08.160
...drunk from the Marquis,
even though he just lost his job.

07:08.280 --> 07:09.600
We don't have any money.

07:11.440 --> 07:13.800
Anyway, he came to bed.

07:14.920 --> 07:16.880
But downstairs,
they must have heard a noise.

07:17.000 --> 07:18.040
They woke up.

07:18.160 --> 07:20.000
They started, er, calling out.

07:21.080 --> 07:22.840
They woke my husband up, and...

07:24.160 --> 07:26.280
...when he's drunk, you don't wake him up.

07:27.680 --> 07:29.920
What happened then, Mrs Connors?

07:31.640 --> 07:33.040
He, erm...

07:33.160 --> 07:34.880
He...

07:35.000 --> 07:36.400
He went downstairs.

07:38.960 --> 07:39.960
He killed them.

07:41.880 --> 07:43.560
Strangled them. All three of them.

07:44.600 --> 07:46.120
(SIGHS)

07:46.240 --> 07:52.880
And you've, erm... You've...you've brought
their bodies here today with you.

07:53.000 --> 07:55.040
Proof, Mr Shelby.

08:06.960 --> 08:08.160
(CHUCKLES)

08:08.280 --> 08:12.000
Their singing was the only pretty thing
in my life.

08:13.800 --> 08:16.560
I don't care my husband beats me...

08:18.040 --> 08:19.520
...but not this.

08:21.880 --> 08:23.160
Mrs Connors.

08:23.280 --> 08:24.360
We have your address.

08:25.560 --> 08:27.840
We will speak to your husband.

08:27.960 --> 08:29.760
My brother here

08:29.880 --> 08:31.920
will go to the Bull Ring market today,

08:32.040 --> 08:34.480
and buy you three new goldfinches,

08:34.600 --> 08:36.680
and have them delivered
to your door.

08:36.800 --> 08:39.240
The same colours
and, you know, feathers.

08:39.360 --> 08:43.440
The new ones I will call
Thomas, Arthur and Finn.

08:44.760 --> 08:46.480
That'll make him pause,

08:46.600 --> 08:48.320
even when he's drunk.

08:49.480 --> 08:50.800
Good day, Mr Shelby.

08:52.000 --> 08:53.400
You take care, Mrs Connors.

08:53.520 --> 08:54.640
Bye.

08:58.800 --> 09:02.520
I don't know how you do this, Tom.
I really don't!

09:02.640 --> 09:04.760
You learn things, Arthur.

09:06.680 --> 09:09.720
That woman
has only two rooms downstairs.

09:09.840 --> 09:13.560
Her husband has lost his job
and he beats her.

09:13.680 --> 09:16.040
And yet, the thing that brings her

09:16.160 --> 09:20.000
to see her Member of Parliament
is songbirds.

09:21.960 --> 09:23.960
Now, that's politics, Arthur.

09:24.080 --> 09:25.800
It's not for me.

09:25.920 --> 09:27.000
Anyway, look.

09:27.120 --> 09:28.560
That list of losers.

09:28.680 --> 09:30.400
How much have we made
on the football?

09:30.520 --> 09:33.960
Ten grand this week.
Finn showing promise, Tom.

09:34.080 --> 09:35.760
Maybe we should put him
on the tracks.

09:35.880 --> 09:37.880
Just a thought.

09:39.200 --> 09:41.120
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

09:41.240 --> 09:42.160
- Finn.
- Yeah.

09:42.280 --> 09:44.320
- Your lunchtime delivery.
- Bring her in.

09:51.800 --> 09:54.680
Tommy, the next fella
wants to see both of you.

09:56.440 --> 09:59.040
- Do you know his face?
- No. He's Chinese.

10:00.440 --> 10:02.200
Chinese in our pub?

10:06.000 --> 10:07.000
Tom...

10:08.320 --> 10:09.520
THOMAS: All right.

10:11.040 --> 10:12.440
Slowly, Micky, let him in.

10:15.920 --> 10:21.440
Three little birds, eh,
Tommy, Finn and Arthur.

10:27.600 --> 10:28.840
Mr Thomas.

10:32.520 --> 10:33.520
Mr Arthur.

10:35.200 --> 10:37.400
(DOOR CLOSES)

10:37.520 --> 10:38.920
(SIGHS)

10:41.920 --> 10:43.960
My name is Brilliant Chang.

10:46.120 --> 10:49.240
Brilliant Chang is dead.

10:49.360 --> 10:50.680
Perhaps.

10:53.120 --> 10:54.840
Sometimes I wonder,

10:54.960 --> 10:56.080
"Is this heaven?"

10:56.200 --> 10:57.240
(CHUCKLES)

10:59.120 --> 11:01.560
Doesn't smell like heaven...

11:01.680 --> 11:04.320
...so I would say I have survived.

11:07.880 --> 11:10.680
- What happened to Maggie?
- You don't like me?

11:12.280 --> 11:14.120
I like everything.

11:17.520 --> 11:21.440
I like fucking everything.

11:23.800 --> 11:25.600
(PHONE RINGS)

11:27.840 --> 11:31.080
You should answer the phone, Mr Shelby.

11:34.280 --> 11:36.560
Micky, bring that phone here now.

11:36.680 --> 11:38.600
(RINGING CONTINUES)

11:40.160 --> 11:41.240
Hello?

11:41.360 --> 11:43.160
FINN: <i>Arthur! Arthur!</i>

11:44.200 --> 11:48.040
I sent a woman with a gun
to your youngest brother's office.

11:48.160 --> 11:49.640
ARTHUR: All right, Finn.

11:49.760 --> 11:50.960
FINN: <i>Right, right.</i>

11:53.600 --> 11:55.400
<i>What the fuck is going on?</i>

11:59.440 --> 12:01.920
Do you want to die again, Chang? Huh?

12:04.040 --> 12:05.200
Good.

12:05.320 --> 12:07.200
The guns are pointed.

12:07.320 --> 12:09.760
Now we are all concentrating.

12:09.880 --> 12:11.680
The moment is now pure.

12:11.800 --> 12:14.040
Purity is not necessary.

12:14.160 --> 12:16.760
Displays are not necessary.

12:16.880 --> 12:22.400
They said, "Tommy Shelby.
That door will need some kicking down."

12:24.400 --> 12:26.960
When you walked through that door,
it was open.

12:28.320 --> 12:30.840
You don't need to do anything
to get my attention.

12:30.960 --> 12:33.720
Now, what exactly do you want?

12:33.840 --> 12:35.000
(SIGHS)

12:39.240 --> 12:41.840
Do you have a match, Mr Shelby?

12:46.320 --> 12:49.160
Anything happens to my brother, Chang...

12:49.280 --> 12:50.920
...you die.

13:05.720 --> 13:08.480
If you die here today,
we'll bury you face down with no hands.

13:08.600 --> 13:12.640
- You'll go straight to hell.
- I don't care about rituals.

13:12.760 --> 13:14.800
I am a rationalist, Mr Shelby.

13:16.000 --> 13:18.120
Well, tell your friend on the phone

13:18.240 --> 13:21.320
to put her gun down
and we can all have a talk.

13:24.640 --> 13:26.080
<i>(GUNSHOT)</i>

13:27.440 --> 13:29.800
Hold your fire, brother!

13:29.920 --> 13:31.640
Hold your fire!

13:34.320 --> 13:35.600
(PANTS)

13:35.720 --> 13:36.960
I'm all right.

13:37.080 --> 13:38.640
She fired into the ceiling.

13:38.760 --> 13:40.640
Finn's all right.

13:40.760 --> 13:42.040
Finn's OK.

13:49.640 --> 13:52.280
Give me your order! Mm.

13:52.400 --> 13:53.920
Give me your order, Tommy!

13:54.040 --> 13:55.080
Yes or no.

13:55.200 --> 13:56.360
At ease.

13:59.520 --> 14:01.880
I said at ease.

14:16.240 --> 14:20.040
May I take something
from my pocket, Mr Shelby?

14:48.840 --> 14:49.920
(COUGHS)

14:52.720 --> 14:57.280
And it's the purest opium
that has ever arrived in Europe.

14:57.400 --> 15:01.200
No salt, no flour, no lies.

15:01.320 --> 15:03.520
Pure truth.

15:04.600 --> 15:06.960
Came off a ship called the <i>Capital,</i>

15:07.080 --> 15:08.720
out of Shanghai.

15:08.840 --> 15:10.680
Docked at Poplar a week ago.

15:11.760 --> 15:13.760
The stevedores
were held at gunpoint,

15:13.880 --> 15:17.880
Chinese unloaded the cargo
by the light of lanterns.

15:19.280 --> 15:24.120
A foreman at the dock estimated there was
seven tonnes of the stuff.

15:24.240 --> 15:27.240
I made a note at the time.

15:31.040 --> 15:32.720
I spoke to that particular foreman

15:32.840 --> 15:35.080
and I worked out that

15:35.200 --> 15:39.000
seven tonnes of pure opium crystals
would be worth...

15:41.120 --> 15:46.480
...approximately, £ 1, 190,000

15:46.600 --> 15:48.320
on international markets.

15:48.440 --> 15:50.080
(CHANG LAUGHS)

15:53.080 --> 15:54.960
The big crash. Hm?

15:56.360 --> 15:58.080
Wall Street.

15:58.200 --> 16:00.920
Now we all keep our ears open
for opportunities.

16:06.720 --> 16:09.160
- What the fuck is going on?
- What are you playing at?

16:09.280 --> 16:10.240
(GUNSHOT)

16:10.360 --> 16:13.360
Finn, we are conducting
a piece of business.

16:13.480 --> 16:15.360
She had a gun to my fucking head!

16:17.440 --> 16:18.480
But your trousers are dry.

16:18.600 --> 16:19.760
You didn't piss yourself.

16:19.880 --> 16:21.920
- He didn't piss himself, Arthur.
- Well done, Finn.

16:22.040 --> 16:25.480
You had a dispute with a lady
and you didn't piss yourself.

16:25.600 --> 16:28.200
And Arthur here tells me
we should put you on the tracks.

16:28.320 --> 16:30.360
Gonna be a good day for you after all,
Finn.

16:30.480 --> 16:31.760
Give me that!

16:31.880 --> 16:33.040
Hey!

16:33.160 --> 16:36.720
Always have your whores
searched at the door.

16:36.840 --> 16:39.160
If I see that bitch on the street,
I'll fucking cut her.

16:39.280 --> 16:41.480
Yeah, all right. All right, come on.

16:41.600 --> 16:43.040
(DOOR CLOSES)

16:47.480 --> 16:49.360
This is a gift, Mr Shelby.

16:51.120 --> 16:53.400
A gesture of goodwill.

17:04.360 --> 17:05.640
I'll throw it in the canal.

17:08.600 --> 17:11.880
Canals are the idea. Right, Chang?

17:38.760 --> 17:41.680
I'm sorry for calling the meeting here,
but the location is part of the deal.

17:41.800 --> 17:44.160
ARTHUR: What fucking deal?

17:44.280 --> 17:47.560
How does it feel
to be barefoot in the mud again, Pol?

17:47.680 --> 17:50.800
It makes me feel young.
What fucking deal?

17:50.920 --> 17:52.000
Four boats.

17:52.120 --> 17:54.040
Four days.

17:54.160 --> 17:56.560
Up the Grand Union from Poplar to here.

17:56.680 --> 18:01.320
Half the cargo is coal
and underneath the coal,

18:01.440 --> 18:02.800
pure opium crystal.

18:02.920 --> 18:05.000
Opium.

18:05.120 --> 18:06.280
I vote against it.

18:07.480 --> 18:08.800
They can't use trucks

18:08.920 --> 18:11.480
because the Chinese drivers
get stopped by the police.

18:11.600 --> 18:12.840
They need to get it out of London

18:12.960 --> 18:15.440
because all the warehouses
are being searched by Customs.

18:15.560 --> 18:18.880
The seven tonnes
is bound for San Francisco,

18:19.000 --> 18:21.960
but the outward ship doesn't sail
for seven days from Liverpool.

18:22.080 --> 18:23.640
They need somewhere safe to store it.

18:23.760 --> 18:27.720
All we have to do is take it up the canal
and keep it here for a week.

18:27.840 --> 18:31.320
We don't fuck with the Chinese, though,
Tom. Dad always said it.

18:31.440 --> 18:35.080
Ask yourself, would he turn down £250,000

18:35.200 --> 18:37.520
to drive four boats up the canal

18:37.640 --> 18:39.560
with no prospect of inspection?

18:41.000 --> 18:43.280
I vote against it, Tom. Hm.

18:43.400 --> 18:45.360
- Mm-mm.
- Polly?

18:45.480 --> 18:48.000
£250,000.

18:48.120 --> 18:51.720
That's half of what Michael lost
in Chicago.

18:51.840 --> 18:54.880
I will ask him to take charge
of this business.

18:55.000 --> 18:57.560
Michael's position will be reinstated
in the company?

18:57.680 --> 19:00.480
His period of quarantine would be over.

19:06.120 --> 19:07.320
Think about it, brother.

19:07.440 --> 19:09.840
Four boats sailing up the cut,

19:09.960 --> 19:12.320
smelling of wood smoke and bacon.

19:14.240 --> 19:16.600
And which one
of Charlie's Gypsy didicoy friends

19:16.720 --> 19:21.240
do you trust, Tom, eh,
with a cargo worth £ 1 million?

19:21.360 --> 19:23.600
I've already made provision.
I'm needed at a meeting.

19:23.720 --> 19:24.720
Let's vote.

19:26.480 --> 19:27.560
Those in favour.

19:35.560 --> 19:36.920
(ARTHUR GRUNTS)

19:38.120 --> 19:42.600
Motion carried.
Arthur, tell Charlie we need four boats

19:42.720 --> 19:45.360
and four tonnes of coal
before it gets dark.

19:45.480 --> 19:46.920
They sail south tonight.

19:48.440 --> 19:52.920
And don't forget to go to the Bull Ring
and get them three songbirds, Arthur.

19:53.040 --> 19:54.200
Yes, Tommy.

19:55.240 --> 19:56.480
Fuck!

20:11.280 --> 20:12.640
What have you heard, Pol?

20:14.880 --> 20:17.160
The man you cut went to the police...

20:19.040 --> 20:20.400
...but we dealt with it.

20:23.760 --> 20:24.800
Is she with him?

20:26.440 --> 20:29.480
If she was, it would be your fault,
Arthur.

20:29.600 --> 20:33.280
But they say his face is so badly cut
he's hard to look at.

20:33.400 --> 20:35.760
So I would say not.

20:35.880 --> 20:42.120
I would also say
it is time to give up on Linda,

20:42.240 --> 20:47.920
find someone else
who might be able to put your fires out.

20:59.960 --> 21:01.720
I can't, though, Pol.

21:04.560 --> 21:06.040
I fucking can't!

21:09.640 --> 21:11.200
And that's it.

21:12.640 --> 21:13.720
That's it.

21:29.080 --> 21:30.680
Whiskey?

21:30.800 --> 21:32.040
Thank you, no.

21:43.440 --> 21:46.880
For reasons I can't divulge,
I need to keep Jimmy McCavern alive.

21:47.000 --> 21:49.920
I've already got a time and a place
for the killing.

21:51.200 --> 21:52.160
You see?

21:53.560 --> 21:56.960
A little alleyway by a shipyard canteen.

21:57.080 --> 22:00.320
A girl called Karen who hates him,
who will give him up.

22:00.440 --> 22:05.200
I have the sound of cranes and winches
to cover the gunshot.

22:05.320 --> 22:07.920
I've got a Bentley to get me away.

22:08.040 --> 22:09.880
The war with the Billy Boys is postponed.

22:10.000 --> 22:13.280
We've made peace.
We're gonna do business together.

22:13.400 --> 22:16.240
When that business is done,
he's all yours.

22:16.360 --> 22:20.840
You can avenge the death of your son
in any way you see fit.

22:20.960 --> 22:22.960
You mean when <i>you</i> say.

22:23.080 --> 22:25.080
When you check
that little stopwatch you've got

22:25.200 --> 22:28.160
that controls the turning of the Earth.

22:29.240 --> 22:30.240
Yeah.

22:31.440 --> 22:33.360
And then you will marry
and you will settle.

22:33.480 --> 22:35.720
Marry? Marry who, Mr Shelby?

22:38.240 --> 22:40.360
Just let me understand you.

22:40.480 --> 22:43.560
Do you mean
that Polly is part of this deal?

22:44.880 --> 22:46.600
Yeah.

22:50.640 --> 22:54.120
Well, Holy Lord God,
Tommy Shelby OBE,

22:54.240 --> 22:56.560
does your vanity have no limits?

22:56.680 --> 22:58.840
I believe it is called the ego these days.

22:58.960 --> 23:00.160
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)
I read books.

23:00.280 --> 23:03.800
You sit on your throne
and you instruct Polly Gray,

23:03.920 --> 23:05.520
who is of far richer blood than you,

23:05.640 --> 23:08.440
as to when she can
and when she can't marry.

23:08.560 --> 23:10.840
Oh, no, she instructs herself.

23:10.960 --> 23:13.000
She has her own strategies.

23:13.120 --> 23:14.520
And we are of the same blood.

23:14.640 --> 23:19.400
She will marry you, but only if you agree
to postpone any attack on McCavern

23:19.520 --> 23:21.120
until this business is done.

23:21.240 --> 23:25.720
So she <i>is</i> some young Gypsy bride
that's yours to give away.

23:25.840 --> 23:29.680
Young she is,
when she's barefoot on the cobbles.

23:29.800 --> 23:32.880
What about a dowry, then, Mr Shelby?
If it's gonna be done in the old way,

23:33.000 --> 23:36.280
well, you know, you throw in
a few coloured ponies or...

23:36.400 --> 23:38.480
I'm having an event at my house.

23:38.600 --> 23:40.120
You are invited.

23:40.240 --> 23:42.160
Polly will be there.

23:42.280 --> 23:45.720
There will be candles and violins

23:45.840 --> 23:47.160
and dancing.

23:47.280 --> 23:50.520
Polly wants you to propose
in the proper way,

23:50.640 --> 23:52.960
and then she will give you
her terms of acceptance.

23:53.080 --> 23:56.440
Inviting you for this purpose
was Polly's idea.

24:03.160 --> 24:05.880
- You can't read?
- I don't read.

24:06.000 --> 24:07.800
- It's <i>Swan Lake.</i>
- Ballet?

24:07.920 --> 24:09.120
Yeah.

24:09.240 --> 24:11.360
Apparently, it's about love.

24:11.480 --> 24:13.640
Polly says that, for now,

24:13.760 --> 24:15.720
love must defeat revenge.

24:38.960 --> 24:41.160
...As a result of the greed and the excess

24:41.280 --> 24:46.480
of a small number of bankers, financiers
and other feckless gamblers.

24:46.600 --> 24:47.760
(MURMURS OF AGREEMENT)

24:47.880 --> 24:49.360
This comprehensive document,

24:49.480 --> 24:53.240
pleading for Government intervention
in all areas of economic life,

24:53.360 --> 24:56.440
represents not just socialism,

24:56.560 --> 25:00.400
but a new breed of National Socialism.

25:00.520 --> 25:01.920
(MURMURS AND GROANS)

25:02.040 --> 25:05.640
And I believe... I believe
that the leaders of my own party

25:05.760 --> 25:08.840
have been very foolish to reject it.

25:08.960 --> 25:10.760
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

25:51.880 --> 25:55.520
How on earth did you get a ballet company
to come to your bloody house?

25:57.040 --> 25:58.760
It's an independent dance company

25:58.880 --> 26:02.200
dedicated to bringing ballet
to the people.

26:02.320 --> 26:04.040
We share a philosophy.

26:04.160 --> 26:05.320
I'm a patron.

26:05.440 --> 26:09.560
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)
I also gave them a lot of money.

26:10.760 --> 26:11.920
Oh.

26:14.040 --> 26:15.680
And this date

26:15.800 --> 26:17.640
is your wife's birthday.

26:18.720 --> 26:19.960
Yeah.

26:21.560 --> 26:23.600
The party is for her.

26:26.080 --> 26:28.240
And she likes ballet, your wife?

26:35.360 --> 26:36.600
Why wouldn't she?

26:38.040 --> 26:39.440
It's just...

26:39.560 --> 26:41.680
Well, you see,
I did some research into her.

26:43.840 --> 26:45.440
Into her past.

26:45.560 --> 26:48.640
If you want to buy her a gift,
she likes diamonds.

26:53.640 --> 26:56.240
Now that we are going to be
conquering the world together,

26:56.360 --> 26:58.720
we need to have no secrets.

26:58.840 --> 27:01.280
We should know
each other's weaknesses.

27:03.520 --> 27:06.040
Your wife has led an interesting life.

27:08.160 --> 27:10.960
It may even be possible that,
as a younger man in Birmingham,

27:11.080 --> 27:13.040
I came across her.

27:14.120 --> 27:18.200
My friends and I would sometimes go
to nightclubs in the south of town.

27:19.600 --> 27:23.320
Well, if you recognise her,
maybe you can talk about old times, eh?

27:25.240 --> 27:28.520
Maybe, if we have met before,
your wife and I

27:28.640 --> 27:30.680
could even renew our acquaintance.

27:32.800 --> 27:34.920
I am invited to stay the night, yes?

27:36.960 --> 27:40.360
I too have done some research,
Sir Oswald.

27:42.120 --> 27:43.160
Yeah.

27:43.280 --> 27:47.880
I researched your wife
and your wife's younger sister

27:48.000 --> 27:51.160
and your wife's stepmother, Lady Curzon,

27:51.280 --> 27:54.000
all of whom you are fucking.

27:54.120 --> 27:56.880
If such things were to take place
on a narrow boat,

27:57.000 --> 27:58.760
the Church would get involved.

27:59.800 --> 28:01.000
But...

28:02.360 --> 28:04.640
...it's not happening on a narrow boat.

28:06.120 --> 28:11.360
No. It's taking place in your apartment,
in your country house,

28:11.480 --> 28:16.800
sometimes even in your office
here in the House of Commons.

28:17.840 --> 28:20.240
So no secrets. And, yes,

28:20.360 --> 28:22.480
yes, you are invited to stay the night

28:22.600 --> 28:26.200
with whichever member of your family
finds favour.

28:26.320 --> 28:29.040
Now, if you don't mind,
I was about to leave,

28:29.160 --> 28:31.480
I need to lock up my office.

28:42.160 --> 28:43.760
Actually, I will come alone.

28:45.360 --> 28:48.160
In society, you are judged
by your hospitality.

28:48.280 --> 28:50.080
I will expect adventure.

29:00.960 --> 29:03.880
Such rogues we are, aren't we?

29:04.000 --> 29:07.040
Sing like songbirds in the House.

29:07.160 --> 29:08.960
And then, afterwards,

29:09.080 --> 29:12.320
relieve ourselves in the bodies
of whomever we choose.

29:15.240 --> 29:18.840
Two men for whom forbidding is forbidden.

29:20.480 --> 29:21.800
It should be quite the party.

29:39.600 --> 29:41.160
(EXHALES)

29:49.960 --> 29:52.200
<i>(SLOW BREA THS)</i>

30:03.720 --> 30:07.120
You have to listen to the voices
that you hear.

30:07.240 --> 30:08.840
Do what they tell you to do.

30:08.960 --> 30:11.560
<i>(BREA THS CONTINUE)</i>

30:11.680 --> 30:14.800
You don't even have to rub the lamp
any more to summon the genie.

30:16.680 --> 30:18.920
It wasn't the blue stone, Tommy.

30:20.520 --> 30:21.520
It was you.

30:24.120 --> 30:25.040
It was you.

30:25.160 --> 30:27.000
<i>(BREA THS AND HEARTBEA TS)</i>

30:30.200 --> 30:32.760
<i>(HEARTBEA TS QUICKEN)</i>

30:45.360 --> 30:47.480
<i>(SLOW BREA THS CONTINUE)</i>

31:06.000 --> 31:07.920
<i>(SLOW BREA THS CONTINUE)</i>

31:36.320 --> 31:39.160
<i>(BANGING ON DOOR)</i>

31:39.280 --> 31:41.520
Who is it?

31:41.640 --> 31:43.280
It's Tommy's car outside.

31:43.400 --> 31:45.120
It's him. I'll get it.

31:53.040 --> 31:54.440
What's happened?

31:54.560 --> 31:56.760
Nothing's happened. I'm all right.

31:56.880 --> 31:57.880
Come in.

32:01.120 --> 32:02.440
Do you want a drink?

32:02.560 --> 32:04.600
- No.
- No?

32:04.720 --> 32:07.360
No. I have some information
for the intelligence officer...

32:08.680 --> 32:10.920
...on conversations with Mosley.

32:11.040 --> 32:14.480
He's planning to put forward proposals
for building works.

32:14.600 --> 32:16.640
He, erm... (CLEARS HIS THROAT)

32:16.760 --> 32:19.720
He wants the Communists to consider
his new party as fraternal,

32:19.840 --> 32:23.320
which means his activities
are now part of your official remit? Yeah?

32:23.440 --> 32:26.280
Mr Shelby, it's 2am.
You can make your report any time.

32:26.400 --> 32:28.960
- Why don't you stay tonight?
- No.

32:32.920 --> 32:34.760
I'll leave you two to...

32:34.880 --> 32:36.480
Yes, good night.

32:36.600 --> 32:37.960
(THOMAS CLEARS HIS THROAT)

32:51.240 --> 32:54.040
I stood on a bridge tonight, Ada.

32:55.320 --> 32:56.320
And I looked down.

32:58.360 --> 32:59.920
And Grace was there...

33:01.560 --> 33:02.680
...but she was still alive.

33:02.800 --> 33:04.640
Tom, have you still been taking laudanum?

33:04.760 --> 33:06.840
The fucking name of the barge
was <i>the January.</i>

33:09.080 --> 33:10.680
Our dad's boat.

33:10.800 --> 33:13.440
The boat I was born on.
We've never got nothing.

33:13.560 --> 33:15.840
We've never got nothing.
And we never fucking will.

33:19.160 --> 33:22.600
Dr Brooke said that you never arrived
for your appointment, Tom.

33:22.720 --> 33:24.160
No.

33:24.280 --> 33:26.960
There's nothing in his books
of any use to a man like me.

33:27.080 --> 33:28.360
They talk about guilt.

33:28.480 --> 33:29.840
Eh?

33:29.960 --> 33:31.880
Guilt! What fucking guilt?

33:32.000 --> 33:34.680
- The black barge.
- No. No, that's not it.

33:34.800 --> 33:36.680
That's not it. He had it right.

33:36.800 --> 33:40.920
Mosley had it right.
He said, "Forbidding is forbidden to us.

33:41.040 --> 33:44.480
"We can do anything.
Nothing can stop us."

33:44.600 --> 33:47.280
But there's a part of me
that is unfamiliar to myself.

33:49.480 --> 33:51.040
And I keep finding myself there.

33:53.280 --> 33:54.960
And only <i>the January can</i> get me away.

33:58.680 --> 34:00.720
Will you at least try
the doctors again, Tom?

34:05.600 --> 34:07.600
Well, then at least throw away your opium.

34:07.720 --> 34:09.240
It's that that causes the visions.

34:09.360 --> 34:11.000
Just...throw it away.

34:11.120 --> 34:12.920
While it's there, it's a temptation.

34:13.040 --> 34:15.480
- (SIGHS)
- How much have you got left?

34:16.720 --> 34:18.040
Seven tonnes.

34:18.160 --> 34:21.400
- Seven tonnes?
- Yeah.

34:26.880 --> 34:28.560
I'd hate for it to run out, Ada.

34:29.800 --> 34:31.000
(SCOFFS)

34:40.360 --> 34:41.520
You do me a favour?

34:44.760 --> 34:49.240
When that kid of yours arrives,
keep it away from me.

35:05.120 --> 35:06.880
A fucking ballet.

35:07.000 --> 35:09.720
He wants to impress someone.

35:09.840 --> 35:11.480
And I'm invited?

35:11.600 --> 35:12.800
You and Gina.

35:14.640 --> 35:15.640
Why?

35:17.440 --> 35:20.720
Because he wants to give you
the chance to come back properly.

35:32.440 --> 35:33.520
Coal haulage?

35:33.640 --> 35:34.880
Yeah.

35:35.000 --> 35:39.040
Tommy wants you to reopen those books
and become managing director.

35:40.080 --> 35:43.600
So I've come back from Detroit
to become a coal man?

35:45.160 --> 35:48.600
The first delivery
is bound for San Francisco,

35:48.720 --> 35:50.160
but if it works...

35:51.240 --> 35:53.920
...Tommy thinks he can find
distribution for it here.

35:56.280 --> 35:59.160
And this, erm, this coal...

36:00.360 --> 36:02.240
- ...is it snow white?
- No.

36:03.520 --> 36:04.880
Golden brown.

36:07.560 --> 36:08.560
Fuck.

36:11.760 --> 36:14.040
This is your opportunity, Michael.

36:14.160 --> 36:17.480
There is more money in this
than there is

36:17.600 --> 36:21.680
in all the other parts of our business
put together.

36:35.040 --> 36:37.160
Tommy knows
what opium does to people.

36:37.280 --> 36:39.760
Tommy knows
what whiskey does to people.

36:39.880 --> 36:41.960
He got an OBE for selling it.

36:45.520 --> 36:47.040
I'll speak to Gina.

36:48.440 --> 36:49.920
(SCOFFS) You'll what?

36:50.040 --> 36:52.520
I will consult my wife.

36:54.320 --> 36:56.840
Your father ran this business
for a bit.

36:56.960 --> 36:58.760
1901.

36:58.880 --> 37:00.640
And he shipped coal. Real coal.

37:00.760 --> 37:02.400
Just coal.

37:02.520 --> 37:08.760
And his fingernails and his eyelids
and his ears were black with it.

37:08.880 --> 37:11.480
And the merchants would offer them
one price

37:11.600 --> 37:13.440
and then only pay half

37:13.560 --> 37:15.360
because they could.

37:15.480 --> 37:18.120
And <i>that was</i> wrong, Michael.

37:41.800 --> 37:46.280
Run your hands through it,
get it under your skin...

37:47.920 --> 37:51.400
...and then see if Gina will let you
lay a finger on her.

37:53.040 --> 37:54.480
(COAL CLATTERS)

37:59.280 --> 38:03.360
I think golden brown
is more to her taste.

38:05.560 --> 38:08.720
Especially when you tell her
how much money you're going to earn.

38:16.000 --> 38:17.840
(DOOR OPENS)

38:19.800 --> 38:21.240
(DOOR CLOSES)

38:30.560 --> 38:32.960
Now we're in business together,
I should ask,

38:33.080 --> 38:36.200
which foot do you kick the ball with,
Mr Shelby?

38:36.320 --> 38:37.480
I have no religion.

38:38.880 --> 38:40.240
Some nights I wish I had.

38:41.480 --> 38:42.480
He's kin?

38:43.640 --> 38:44.640
Yeah.

38:46.120 --> 38:47.400
And the simple fellow?

38:48.680 --> 38:51.160
He's a lot less simple
than you might at first think.

38:53.080 --> 38:54.120
Do you trust them?

39:00.440 --> 39:02.160
Right. So I take a boatload.

39:03.320 --> 39:04.600
No.

39:04.720 --> 39:08.440
Ten sacks to start with,
so you can test the market.

39:08.560 --> 39:10.640
Then we'll deal in boatloads.

39:10.760 --> 39:13.320
Cash payment on loading.

39:13.440 --> 39:14.600
£ 1 O,000.

39:16.120 --> 39:18.440
For that amount,
it'll have to be a cheque.

39:18.560 --> 39:19.760
I don't take cheques.

39:23.360 --> 39:24.720
It'll be a cheque.

39:28.520 --> 39:29.520
I will take a cheque

39:29.640 --> 39:31.880
if it's guaranteed
by our mutual friend in London,

39:32.000 --> 39:33.000
Mr Mosley.

39:44.280 --> 39:45.960
(CHUCKLES)

39:46.080 --> 39:48.400
Well, who would've thought
I'd be doing business

39:48.520 --> 39:51.400
with fucking Gypsy Catholic scum?

39:53.760 --> 39:57.000
Yeah, who'd have thought,
eh, Charlie?

39:57.120 --> 39:58.600
CHARLIE: Who would have thought it?

39:58.720 --> 40:01.040
Aye, but you're OK.

40:01.160 --> 40:04.640
THOMAS: Yeah, I'm only OK
until I'm not OK.

40:04.760 --> 40:06.880
Then I'm really not.

40:08.920 --> 40:11.480
Delivery in seven days.

40:13.880 --> 40:15.000
Cheque guaranteed.

40:15.120 --> 40:18.400
Won't your Chinese friends
expect the seven tonnes that leaves London

40:18.520 --> 40:20.840
to still be seven tonnes
when it reaches Liverpool?

40:20.960 --> 40:23.680
You leave that to me, Mr McCavern.

40:23.800 --> 40:27.520
Oh, you mean you're bold enough
to skim the Chinese? (CHUCKLES)

40:30.000 --> 40:33.120
You have some kind of death wish,
Mr Shelby?

40:51.040 --> 40:54.120
An evening with a tribe of Gypsies.

40:57.080 --> 40:59.720
When you've unpacked,
there should be a girl laid on for you.

41:01.160 --> 41:02.480
Mr Shelby is a socialist

41:02.600 --> 41:05.000
and believes in equality of service
for all classes.

41:15.560 --> 41:19.960
According to the invitation,
there'll be an interval at nine o'clock.

41:20.080 --> 41:22.080
Say that you're feeling tired
and we'll leave.

41:23.760 --> 41:27.720
Well, if you see a duke,
introduce me.

41:27.840 --> 41:29.840
My God, at last!

41:29.960 --> 41:31.880
Something you like about England.

41:34.960 --> 41:37.720
Gina, I've been made an offer.

41:40.360 --> 41:42.560
To come back into the company.

41:42.680 --> 41:43.960
Michael, we agreed,

41:44.080 --> 41:46.920
the baby will be born in New York.
Remember?

41:47.040 --> 41:48.240
The job is haulage.

41:49.400 --> 41:50.960
Supply. Transport.

41:52.960 --> 41:53.960
Opium.

41:58.400 --> 42:00.800
- Tommy has made contact...
- Tommy!

42:01.920 --> 42:04.520
Tommy has made contact
with Chinese suppliers

42:04.640 --> 42:06.440
who have plantations in the Afghan hills.

42:08.160 --> 42:09.160
Pure grade.

42:11.200 --> 42:14.200
We will take delivery
and ship it all over Europe.

42:15.960 --> 42:16.960
You mean heroin?

42:19.040 --> 42:20.040
Yes.

42:23.080 --> 42:24.600
And how much would you make?

42:26.000 --> 42:29.840
Conservative estimate,
three shipments a year from Shanghai,

42:29.960 --> 42:31.480
seven tonnes each,

42:31.600 --> 42:34.160
stand to make approximately
£ 1 million.

42:34.280 --> 42:35.280
Per annum.

42:37.320 --> 42:38.920
The company will make three.

42:43.080 --> 42:45.520
We could go to New York
whenever we wanted.

42:45.640 --> 42:48.080
On our own fucking plane.

42:51.480 --> 42:54.560
- We always have to come back, right?
- Yes.

42:54.680 --> 42:56.640
For £ 1 million a year, we do.

42:59.680 --> 43:02.240
What happens if you get caught?

43:02.360 --> 43:03.440
Tommy has friends.

43:05.280 --> 43:08.400
If the ship gets stopped,
it'll be the Chinese who hang.

43:10.600 --> 43:12.240
Think about it, Gina.

43:14.520 --> 43:16.360
When we move into our house...

43:17.560 --> 43:21.360
...our room for entertaining
will be twice this size.

43:25.320 --> 43:26.320
Will it now?

43:29.720 --> 43:31.840
The magazines say that

43:31.960 --> 43:35.160
it's all straight lines and simplicity
in the 1930s.

43:36.760 --> 43:37.800
Deco is dead.

43:41.400 --> 43:44.160
We'll be able to afford
dukes and duchesses.

43:46.120 --> 43:47.760
And maybe...

43:47.880 --> 43:49.480
...maybe a princess or two.

43:51.600 --> 43:53.920
And the painting on the wall
will be of you.

43:55.560 --> 43:58.240
Because Tommy Shelby will be gone

43:58.360 --> 44:01.120
and it will be Michael Gray
arranging the ballet.

44:03.600 --> 44:04.720
Where will Tommy be?

44:06.960 --> 44:08.520
Where he wants to go to most.

44:11.560 --> 44:12.960
<i>Ah.</i>

44:14.600 --> 44:15.600
There.

44:16.680 --> 44:18.840
A lord.

44:18.960 --> 44:22.000
Actually, I think Mr Mosley's a baronet.

44:28.280 --> 44:30.040
Where the fuck is Tommy anyway?

44:46.000 --> 44:47.080
Tommy...

44:47.200 --> 44:49.560
(GROANS) My house.

44:49.680 --> 44:52.000
- My wife.
- (MOANS)

44:52.120 --> 44:53.280
Let 'em wait.

44:58.120 --> 44:59.120
Sir Oswald.

45:01.640 --> 45:04.240
Do I not get announced?

45:04.360 --> 45:05.800
Mr Shelby asked me to tell you

45:05.920 --> 45:09.080
that he's busy
with the catering preparations

45:09.200 --> 45:11.040
and will be joining you shortly.

45:12.560 --> 45:15.040
In the meantime,
and while you're waiting,

45:15.160 --> 45:18.280
we have opium, cocaine and brandy.

45:20.200 --> 45:23.440
I don't use opium or cocaine,

45:23.560 --> 45:26.200
and brandy is for after dinner,
not before.

45:27.800 --> 45:31.440
I also have a list of options
for the end of the evening.

45:31.560 --> 45:35.040
You'll notice that
the maids wear name tags.

45:36.360 --> 45:38.000
We hired them specially...

45:39.160 --> 45:42.040
...for those guests staying the night.

45:42.160 --> 45:46.440
All things are available
except the ballerinas.

45:49.120 --> 45:51.040
And who, might I ask, are you?

45:53.160 --> 45:55.680
I am a queen amongst the Romanies.

45:57.040 --> 45:59.440
And I too am unavailable.

46:09.000 --> 46:10.360
Lizzie.

46:10.480 --> 46:13.760
There's something I didn't tell you
about this evening.

46:13.880 --> 46:15.600
Something about our guest.

46:15.720 --> 46:17.120
Mosley.

46:19.920 --> 46:21.680
It's possible that...

46:21.800 --> 46:23.600
...that you've met him before.

46:23.720 --> 46:24.720
Before when?

46:27.000 --> 46:29.440
Before you became who you are.

46:31.960 --> 46:34.400
Would you even remember him?

46:34.520 --> 46:36.320
Would he remember you?

46:38.600 --> 46:41.560
All I remember is,
I drank too much champagne.

46:41.680 --> 46:43.200
I wasn't taking cash.

46:46.600 --> 46:47.600
Lizzie...

46:50.720 --> 46:52.120
There's a pile of bodies...

46:53.280 --> 46:54.480
...floating by.

46:55.560 --> 46:56.680
Let 'em go, Lizzie.

46:58.560 --> 46:59.760
Let 'em go.

47:03.800 --> 47:05.720
So that's why you brought me
in here.

47:05.840 --> 47:07.520
To lay your claim.

47:09.480 --> 47:10.480
Yeah.

47:14.480 --> 47:16.360
Well, it's a start, I suppose.

47:18.440 --> 47:24.640
He lays a fucking hand on you,
he will be meat for Johnny Dogs.

47:29.000 --> 47:30.840
You were indisposed when I arrived.

47:38.840 --> 47:43.400
In society, you greet a guest,
you don't leave them hanging...

47:43.520 --> 47:45.680
...looking around like a fucking dog.

47:45.800 --> 47:49.880
(CLEARS HIS THROAT) Before we join
the others, I have some business.

47:50.000 --> 47:51.280
I need a signature.

47:51.400 --> 47:54.840
By the way,
your brandy before dinner thing amuses me,

47:54.960 --> 47:57.600
but none of the maids are of interest.

47:57.720 --> 47:59.880
And I despise the use of drugs.

48:00.920 --> 48:03.960
Your strategies are very transparent.

48:05.280 --> 48:08.360
I'm involved in a transaction
with Jimmy McCavern,

48:08.480 --> 48:10.840
your acquaintance from the north.

48:10.960 --> 48:13.000
I have no idea who you mean.

48:13.120 --> 48:15.440
I don't trust him.
He wants to pay by cheque.

48:15.560 --> 48:18.960
I need your signature
as a guarantor on the transaction

48:19.080 --> 48:20.840
should his cheque fail to be honoured.

48:20.960 --> 48:22.880
The sum is £ 1 O,000.

48:23.000 --> 48:25.080
And what is it he's buying from you?

48:25.200 --> 48:26.280
A gin distillery.

48:26.400 --> 48:28.320
He's buying my old one.
I'm buying a new one.

48:29.440 --> 48:30.640
Hmm.

48:34.160 --> 48:35.840
So not only is the truce holding,

48:35.960 --> 48:38.440
but you two
are actually doing business.

48:38.560 --> 48:41.160
Yeah. But I still don't trust his cheques.

48:44.000 --> 48:46.080
If I sign a cheque guarantee
for this man,

48:46.200 --> 48:48.840
it is proof of a connection
between me and him.

48:48.960 --> 48:51.200
Something you could later use
against me.

48:53.640 --> 48:55.600
Why would I want to move against you?

49:12.240 --> 49:14.320
You're curious about my weaknesses.

49:16.480 --> 49:19.560
And you've learned it's not cocaine,

49:19.680 --> 49:21.400
not maids.

49:30.960 --> 49:35.520
But now you will learn my weakness
is a tendency to trust people.

49:35.640 --> 49:37.040
Do you have a pen?

49:50.680 --> 49:52.000
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

49:53.120 --> 49:54.120
Mr Shelby.

49:56.200 --> 49:58.200
I know you have no classical education,

49:58.320 --> 50:01.400
but just realised you are
the perfect balance between the gods

50:01.520 --> 50:03.480
Dionysus and Apollo.

50:03.600 --> 50:07.760
Irrational frenzy
controlled by reason and self reflection.

50:09.840 --> 50:13.720
Do you know the work
of Fried rich Nietzsche?

50:13.840 --> 50:15.680
- No.
- Freud?

50:15.800 --> 50:17.120
Yes.

50:17.240 --> 50:18.720
<i>Ah.</i>

50:23.680 --> 50:24.880
There.

50:25.000 --> 50:27.240
Your guarantee of trust.

50:29.000 --> 50:32.280
Now perhaps you would introduce me
to your wonderful wife.

50:37.200 --> 50:39.080
So, did you know?

50:39.200 --> 50:40.880
What?

50:41.000 --> 50:43.240
Oh, that tonight's special guest
might have fucked you

50:43.360 --> 50:45.440
when you were a nightclub hostess?

50:45.560 --> 50:46.560
Yeah.

50:48.360 --> 50:51.040
Lizzie, if we were to strike
from our guest lists

50:51.160 --> 50:53.600
every man in Birmingham who you...

50:56.240 --> 50:58.160
- Yes or no?
- Fucking yes.

50:58.280 --> 50:59.280
Shit.

51:03.240 --> 51:06.680
Sir Oswald,
this is my wife Elizabeth.

51:06.800 --> 51:08.680
Lizzie, Sir Oswald Mosley.

51:11.160 --> 51:12.680
Since we all appear to know,

51:12.800 --> 51:15.040
and since knowledge is permission,

51:15.160 --> 51:19.240
I'm sure, Mr Shelby, in the spirit
of our honest relationship,

51:19.360 --> 51:21.040
you won't mind me saying

51:21.160 --> 51:23.880
it was a bottle of Champagne
and an evening well spent.

51:26.000 --> 51:28.760
Actually, it was an evening wasted.

51:30.320 --> 51:33.000
For the Champagne
and brandy you bought me,

51:33.120 --> 51:37.440
as I recall, it was the booze that put you
to sleep a little prematurely.

51:37.560 --> 51:42.360
MAN: Ladies and gentlemen,
the dance is about to begin.

51:46.880 --> 51:48.800
Mr Mosley!

51:48.920 --> 51:51.120
A toast, if I may.

51:51.240 --> 51:53.760
To the end of our deal,

51:53.880 --> 51:56.280
and the beginning of something more.

51:56.400 --> 51:58.200
Happy Birthday, Lizzie.

52:02.720 --> 52:03.720
This way.

52:09.440 --> 52:12.120
(CLASSICAL MUSIC)

52:37.440 --> 52:39.160
(SNORES)

53:31.840 --> 53:35.120
Polly Gray, Gypsy queen,

53:35.240 --> 53:36.880
will you marry me,

53:37.000 --> 53:39.400
a poor commoner who loves you?

54:35.360 --> 54:40.400
Let's fuck before the swan dies.

55:11.040 --> 55:13.960
I heard there was a family occasion.

55:18.360 --> 55:20.360
Look, I'm sorry, Linda.

55:20.480 --> 55:22.960
That animal inside me,

55:23.080 --> 55:25.640
it comes out and I can't stop it.

55:27.560 --> 55:29.320
Fuck, Linda.

55:29.440 --> 55:31.160
Without you, I c...

55:31.280 --> 55:33.280
Come inside, please.

55:35.240 --> 55:37.000
His name was Frederick.

55:37.120 --> 55:39.440
All we ever did was talk, Arthur.

55:39.560 --> 55:40.880
He just listened.

55:42.560 --> 55:44.600
And now he has no face.

55:52.640 --> 55:56.120
He's as ugly on the outside
as you are on the inside.

56:04.960 --> 56:06.960
May you Peaky Blinders all rot...

56:08.120 --> 56:09.600
...in fucking hell.

56:12.440 --> 56:14.360
(GUNSHOT)

56:21.160 --> 56:23.840
- Arthur...
- (APPLAUSE IN DISTANCE)

56:33.320 --> 56:35.840
(APPLAUSE CONTINUES)

56:35.864 --> 56:40.864
http://hiqve.com/
